# SCSS Styling Guidelines

## CSS Modules

- Use CSS modules for component-specific styles
- File naming: `index.module.scss`
- Import as: `import styles from "./index.module.scss"`

## Class Naming

- Use kebab-case for class names
- Use descriptive names that reflect component structure
- Follow BEM methodology when appropriate

```scss
.app-header {
  width: 100%;
  background: #ffffff;
  
  .main-header {
    width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    
    .top-header {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      height: 74px;
    }
  }
}
```

## Layout Patterns

- Use flexbox for layout: `display: flex`
- Common container width: `1200px` with `margin: 0 auto`
- Standard spacing units based on design system

## Colors

- Primary color: `#3ca7fa` (theme color)
- Background: `#ffffff`
- Borders: `#f1f2fa`
- Text colors follow design system

## Responsive Design

- Use media queries for responsive behavior
- Follow mobile-first approach when needed
- Consider standard breakpoints

## File Organization

- One component per SCSS file
- Global styles in [index.scss](mdc:src/index.scss)
- Component styles in `index.module.scss`
- Import global styles in [main.tsx](mdc:src/main.tsx)
